					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-1926280#post-2661104</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-1926280/inside-outside#post-2661104</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Mon, 26 Sep 2016 17:49:13 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>CirclesAndSquares</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1367458</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>This made me feel similarly as reading House of Leaves. This tale is uncomfortable and confusing and very, very good.</p> <p>+1</p> <p>There's a typo, i believe: The running continued for a long time. Doors were opened, rooms were crossed, halls were walked, but no exit. No exit. <strong>They</strong> was no out. Was there an outside? Did an outside even exist? There may not be, but Dr. Watkins kept going.</p> <p>I would have fixed it, but i'm squeamish about editing to work of others.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
